John Hopkins Beats Hofstra 12-5 to Open NCAA Lacrosse Tournament

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-05-14T18:16:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-14/john-hopkins-beats-hofstra-12-5-to-open-ncaa-lacrosse-tournament.html
Johns Hopkins University beat Hofstra
University 12-5 in the opening game of the National Collegiate
Athletic Association men’s lacrosse championship.  Third-seeded Hopkins scored the final six goals of the game
in Baltimore after Hofstra pulled within 6-5 in the third
quarter. The Blue Jays advance to meet Denver or Villanova in
the quarterfinals.  Fourth-seeded  Notre Dame  meets  Pennsylvania , No. 5 Duke
plays Delaware and No. 2 Cornell faces Hartford in today’s other
first-round games.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  